  "mixStrategy": "This relaxation electronic/house arrangement in Cm uses a gentle, spacious approach with three tracks occupying distinct frequency bands. BASS (Synth Bass, 20-300Hz): Provides the low-end foundation with slow, pumping root-octave patterns on C2/G2 following the chord progression i\u2192bVI\u2192bVII\u2192i (Cm\u2192Ab\u2192Bb\u2192Cm). The bass uses long sustains and gentle velocity (40-60) to create a warm, pillowy low end rather than aggressive pumping. It locks to half-note and whole-note rhythms. CHORDS (Warm Pad, 300Hz-2kHz): Sustained minor chord voicings in the C3-C5 range with very long holds (3-6 seconds), creating a dreamy harmonic bed. Chords shift slowly following the same progression, with velocity 40-55 for a floating, ambient quality. Filter-sweep feel is achieved through gradual velocity changes. MELODY (Sawtooth Lead, 1-8kHz): Gentle arpeggiated patterns in C4-C6 range using chord tones on strong beats and scale passing tones on weak beats. Velocity stays soft (40-60) with moderate note density \u2014 enough to create gentle motion without urgency. The melody breathes with rests between phrases. ENERGY ARC: Segments (~7.5s each): 0.3\u21920.5\u21920.6\u21920.7\u21920.6\u21920.4. The piece opens sparse and quiet, builds gently to a warm peak around 22-30s, then gracefully fades. All tracks crescendo and decrescendo together. The chord progression cycles as: Cm(i) for 2 bars \u2192 Ab(bVI) for 1 bar \u2192 Bb(bVII) for 1 bar \u2192 repeat. At 61 BPM, one bar \u2248 3.93s. The 4-bar cycle \u2248 15.74s, giving roughly 3 full cycles in 45 seconds. All tracks change chords at the same moments, creating unity.",
